1
00:00:42,022 --> 00:00:46,068
MY ROYAL NEMESIS

2
00:01:15,430 --> 00:01:17,224
Why do you stare at it so intently?

3
00:01:20,602 --> 00:01:23,855
Does a plum blossom flowering
in midsummer unsettle you so?

4
00:01:25,440 --> 00:01:27,234
No, it is not that.

5
00:01:35,200 --> 00:01:37,661
Flowers that bloom in season are no fun.

6
00:01:38,203 --> 00:01:40,956
I want nothing less that a plum blossom
amid midwinter snow

7
00:01:41,998 --> 00:01:43,667
if I am to see any charm in it.

8
00:01:44,251 --> 00:01:45,585
<i>Did you hear?</i>

9
00:01:45,669 --> 00:01:49,172
<i>A marriage proposal was delivered</i>
<i>to Seonghyeon Pavilion this morning.</i>

10
00:01:49,256 --> 00:01:51,174
<i>I guess the prince is getting married.</i>

11
00:01:58,181 --> 00:01:59,516
Dry this by the window.

12
00:02:01,309 --> 00:02:02,394
Yes, Your Highness.

13
00:02:18,869 --> 00:02:20,871
-It is raining.
-Leave it.

14
00:02:36,928 --> 00:02:38,889
Do you like the rain?

15
00:02:40,223 --> 00:02:42,142
Why? Do you dislike it?

16
00:02:42,225 --> 00:02:43,602
What is there to like?

17
00:02:44,186 --> 00:02:45,687
The mud gets everywhere,

18
00:02:45,771 --> 00:02:47,314
my skirt gets soaked,

19
00:02:48,190 --> 00:02:49,733
and the laundry piles up.

20
00:02:50,317 --> 00:02:53,028
I doubt any court lady likes the rain.

21
00:02:58,033 --> 00:02:59,159
Is that so?

22
00:03:07,042 --> 00:03:08,210
Your Highness!

23
00:03:19,304 --> 00:03:20,806
Please go back inside.

24
00:03:22,140 --> 00:03:24,226
You will catch a cold at this rate.

25
00:03:32,275 --> 00:03:33,276
Stay still.

26
00:03:39,449 --> 00:03:41,243
Now feel it for yourself.

27
00:03:41,827 --> 00:03:43,078
This cleansing chill.

28
00:04:04,307 --> 00:04:05,392
Gosh.

29
00:04:05,934 --> 00:04:08,687
A second cleanse might leave me bedridden.

30
00:04:09,521 --> 00:04:11,815
A little rain will not kill you.

31
00:04:15,193 --> 00:04:16,361
Then again,

32
00:04:17,320 --> 00:04:19,030
it must be different for a woman.

33
00:04:36,882 --> 00:04:38,508
Why are you just standing there?

34
00:04:39,342 --> 00:04:40,844
Hurry up and run.

35
00:04:43,346 --> 00:04:44,931
<i>What do you think you're doing?</i>

36
00:04:49,394 --> 00:04:51,688
Protecting you. I gave you my word.

37
00:04:53,064 --> 00:04:54,649
You sure this is protecting me?

38
00:04:55,567 --> 00:04:57,319
Or are we just going down together?

39
00:05:03,658 --> 00:05:04,910
It is fine

40
00:05:05,827 --> 00:05:07,495
if we are together.

41
00:05:09,414 --> 00:05:10,498
What

42
00:05:10,582 --> 00:05:12,208
are you doing?

43
00:05:15,795 --> 00:05:17,631
It really is shining.

44
00:05:20,091 --> 00:05:21,343
Now that I am with you.

45
00:05:42,405 --> 00:05:45,659
EPISODE 8
SCREW THIS WORLD

46
00:05:46,284 --> 00:05:48,244
-Look. They're coming out.
-There they are!

47
00:05:48,328 --> 00:05:49,955
-They're coming out!
-Over there!

48
00:05:52,082 --> 00:05:52,999
Listen here!

49
00:05:53,083 --> 00:05:54,960
I shall explain everything.

50
00:05:55,043 --> 00:05:56,169
-That woman…
-Shin Seo-ri.

51
00:05:56,252 --> 00:05:57,587
-Isn't she that model?
-That model.

52
00:05:57,671 --> 00:05:58,630
That is right!

53
00:05:58,713 --> 00:06:00,507
I am the one from the rumors.

54
00:06:00,590 --> 00:06:01,716
I am Shin Seo-ri.

55
00:06:02,509 --> 00:06:03,843
Are you insane?

56
00:06:03,927 --> 00:06:05,637
Mr. Cha Se-gye here

57
00:06:05,720 --> 00:06:07,764
is the chief of my agency.

58
00:06:07,847 --> 00:06:08,932
First, I can say

59
00:06:09,015 --> 00:06:11,309
Mr. Cha did not touch
a drop of alcohol that night.

60
00:06:11,393 --> 00:06:13,478
I swear that on my life.

61
00:06:13,561 --> 00:06:14,604
That night,

62
00:06:14,688 --> 00:06:16,898
he just accompanied me
in a management capacity.

63
00:06:16,982 --> 00:06:18,274
I would like to deeply apologize

64
00:06:19,401 --> 00:06:20,735
for causing this misunderstanding.

65
00:06:20,819 --> 00:06:22,779
Misunderstanding?
Are you denying the scandal?

66
00:06:22,862 --> 00:06:25,615
Then why did you two go
to the beach alone at night?

67
00:06:25,699 --> 00:06:28,118
We only returned to the set
in the dead of night…

68
00:06:31,121 --> 00:06:32,038
for this beach stone.

69
00:06:32,122 --> 00:06:33,832
-A beach stone?
-What is that?

70
00:06:34,457 --> 00:06:37,038
A beach stone? Isn't that just a rock?

71
00:06:37,127 --> 00:06:39,838
Under the guidance of Mr. Cha,
who was worried about the fine

72
00:06:39,921 --> 00:06:41,840
we could have incurred
due to their removal,

73
00:06:41,923 --> 00:06:43,787
we returned the stones
to their rightful place.

74
00:06:43,887 --> 00:06:45,137
But I was severely intoxicated,

75
00:06:45,218 --> 00:06:46,886
and I managed to forget this one.

76
00:06:47,512 --> 00:06:50,098
I vow to return
this beach stone promptly as well.

77
00:06:50,724 --> 00:06:52,058
And to clear the air,

78
00:06:52,142 --> 00:06:54,394
I wish to now bring to light the good deed

79
00:06:54,477 --> 00:06:56,146
Mr. Cha had wished to keep quiet.

80
00:06:58,732 --> 00:07:00,233
Good deed? What good deed?

81
00:07:00,775 --> 00:07:02,068
Mr. Cha Se-gye

82
00:07:02,152 --> 00:07:05,363
will donate half of the profits
from this commercial shoot

83
00:07:05,447 --> 00:07:07,782
to the conservation
of Tamna Island's natural heritage.

84
00:07:07,866 --> 00:07:09,492
Nothing short of magnanimous.

85
00:07:10,035 --> 00:07:11,036
I will?

86
00:07:11,119 --> 00:07:12,620
Wow.

87
00:07:17,208 --> 00:07:18,084
Yes.

88
00:07:18,668 --> 00:07:21,838
As Biojei is a company
with eco-friendliness as its core slogan,

89
00:07:21,921 --> 00:07:24,382
we plan to lead the way
on eco-friendly policy.

90
00:07:24,466 --> 00:07:25,592
"Eco-friendly"?

91
00:07:27,093 --> 00:07:29,429
That is also why we chose Jeju
and its pristine nature

92
00:07:29,512 --> 00:07:30,680
as the backdrop

93
00:07:30,764 --> 00:07:33,475
for the ad campaign
of our newly launched Dynaestie line.

94
00:07:34,309 --> 00:07:35,852
<i>Look at them perfectly in sync.</i>

95
00:07:35,935 --> 00:07:37,645
And there is one more important fact.

96
00:07:37,729 --> 00:07:40,398
I already have a beloved.

97
00:07:40,482 --> 00:07:42,067
-What?
-All of a sudden?

98
00:07:42,150 --> 00:07:43,651
He possesses a face as fine as jade

99
00:07:43,735 --> 00:07:45,987
and a character as noble as a crane.

100
00:07:46,071 --> 00:07:47,697
Therefore, we ask that you all refrain

101
00:07:47,781 --> 00:07:50,658
from engaging in speculation and rumors
regarding this matter.

102
00:07:50,742 --> 00:07:52,077
Now, please excuse me.

103
00:07:52,160 --> 00:07:53,203
Until next time.

104
00:07:53,286 --> 00:07:55,163
-Ms. Shin!
-Wait, Ms. Shin!

105
00:07:59,375 --> 00:08:00,835
Now then. A further detailed statement

106
00:08:00,919 --> 00:08:03,588
will be delivered through our PR team.

107
00:08:03,671 --> 00:08:05,215
POWER-TRIPPING CEO'S SUDDEN PIVOT?

108
00:08:05,298 --> 00:08:06,841
CAN THIS DONATION SAVE HIM NOW?

109
00:08:07,383 --> 00:08:09,260
…ACQUIRES ENTERTAINMENT AGENCY
IN QUESTIONABLE MOVE

110
00:08:09,344 --> 00:08:10,970
UNKNOWN ACTRESS
DECLARES SHE HAS A LOVER

111
00:08:11,054 --> 00:08:12,472
UNWANTED CONFESSION
SPARKS CONTROVERSY

112
00:08:17,727 --> 00:08:18,895
Have you lost your damn mind?

113
00:08:18,978 --> 00:08:20,934
Are you trying to blow yourself up?

114
00:08:21,272 --> 00:08:22,357
Dimwits.

115
00:08:22,440 --> 00:08:24,317
It appears the stratagem worked.

116
00:08:25,026 --> 00:08:27,695
-What stratagem?
-The 35th Stratagem: The Chain Stratagem.

117
00:08:27,779 --> 00:08:30,657
First, I used the Beauty Trap
to distract the enemy's gaze.

118
00:08:30,740 --> 00:08:32,867
Then, the Self-Injury to reverse our odds.

119
00:08:32,951 --> 00:08:35,829
I chained these stratagems together
to buy us time.

120
00:08:36,454 --> 00:08:38,414
And now we seize
this opening to plot our reversal.

121
00:08:38,498 --> 00:08:39,999
Stratagems, my ass.

122
00:08:40,083 --> 00:08:41,000
And the donation?

123
00:08:41,084 --> 00:08:43,628
Half the profits? Do you have
any idea how much that actually is?

124
00:08:43,711 --> 00:08:45,296
Do I need to know?

125
00:08:45,380 --> 00:08:47,340
The rich are always the ones
most obsessed with money.

126
00:08:47,423 --> 00:08:50,051
Everyone's already watching
to see when I'll fail.

127
00:08:50,135 --> 00:08:52,971
Whether I donate or not,
whether the agency tanks or not.

128
00:08:53,054 --> 00:08:54,973
Now they're going
to scrutinize all of that too.

129
00:08:55,056 --> 00:08:56,349
That is just your imagination.

130
00:08:56,432 --> 00:08:58,726
You really think the whole world
revolves around you.

131
00:08:58,810 --> 00:09:00,145
That is enough idle chatter.

132
00:09:00,228 --> 00:09:01,896
Let us go get a bite to eat now.

133
00:09:04,524 --> 00:09:06,442
I'm about to be robbed
of my hard-earned money.

134
00:09:06,526 --> 00:09:08,027
You think I have an appetite?

135
00:09:14,033 --> 00:09:15,076
You are eating just fine.

136
00:09:15,160 --> 00:09:17,453
You can't enjoy anything
on an empty stomach.

137
00:09:20,540 --> 00:09:21,583
So what now?

138
00:09:22,167 --> 00:09:23,877
I would've just handled it all on my own.

139
00:09:23,960 --> 00:09:26,212
Why did you have to butt in
and complicate everything?

140
00:09:26,296 --> 00:09:27,630
Was I supposed to do nothing?

141
00:09:27,714 --> 00:09:30,717
You were about to be
unjustly torn apart by a pack of wolves.

142
00:09:31,342 --> 00:09:32,969
I came all this way to save you.

143
00:09:34,429 --> 00:09:35,346
Save me?

144
00:09:39,309 --> 00:09:41,352
I really thought
some grand declaration was coming.

145
00:09:41,436 --> 00:09:43,271
I almost had a heart attack.

146
00:09:43,354 --> 00:09:45,148
Were you expecting, "I am his woman"?

147
00:09:45,231 --> 00:09:47,150
Were you terrified
I would publicly announce that?

148
00:09:47,233 --> 00:09:48,526
Of course I was terrified.

149
00:09:48,610 --> 00:09:50,987
Afraid you'd get dragged
through the mud with me.

150
00:09:51,821 --> 00:09:52,780
It scared me.

151
00:09:57,827 --> 00:09:59,245
I have a brain, you know.

152
00:09:59,329 --> 00:10:00,705
I would not be so reckless.

153
00:10:01,289 --> 00:10:03,208
I am done being "someone's woman."

154
00:10:03,750 --> 00:10:06,127
I want no part of such a label.

155
00:10:06,211 --> 00:10:07,212
Label?

156
00:10:08,379 --> 00:10:10,006
<i>Dan-sim of the Kang clan.</i>

157
00:10:10,089 --> 00:10:11,341
How did such a precious treasure

158
00:10:11,424 --> 00:10:13,134
end up in your possession?

159
00:10:13,218 --> 00:10:14,677
That is…

160
00:10:14,761 --> 00:10:16,262
a personal possession.

161
00:10:16,346 --> 00:10:19,349
This jade is so prized that it is offered
as imperial tribute even in Qing.

162
00:10:19,432 --> 00:10:21,226
How dare you lie to me!

163
00:10:21,309 --> 00:10:22,727
Hear me!

164
00:10:22,810 --> 00:10:25,480
-Drag her out and flog her!
-Yes, ma'am.

165
00:10:25,563 --> 00:10:27,899
Ma'am, may I have a moment?

166
00:10:34,072 --> 00:10:35,573
You just need to say one thing.

167
00:10:35,657 --> 00:10:38,368
If you do, I shall provide you
with a means to survive.

168
00:10:39,160 --> 00:10:41,412
Declare that you lay
with the Grand Prince.

169
00:10:51,673 --> 00:10:53,466
Your silence says it all.

170
00:10:53,549 --> 00:10:56,344
You have already given him
your heart. Foolish girl.

171
00:10:56,427 --> 00:10:59,555
Do you believe you are the only one
who has caught his eye?

172
00:10:59,639 --> 00:11:01,349
This palace is rife

173
00:11:01,432 --> 00:11:03,226
with lonely court ladies such as yourself.

174
00:11:03,309 --> 00:11:05,520
Whispering honeyed words
is effortless for a man.

175
00:11:05,603 --> 00:11:08,022
That cannot be true.
His Highness would not--

176
00:11:08,106 --> 00:11:09,190
It is clear

177
00:11:09,857 --> 00:11:11,442
you have yet to come to your senses.

178
00:11:11,526 --> 00:11:14,279
As long as the Grand Prince
remains out of his brother's favor,

179
00:11:14,362 --> 00:11:15,530
he will not survive.

180
00:11:16,239 --> 00:11:17,532
So make your choice.

181
00:11:17,615 --> 00:11:20,493
Die as the Grand Prince's beloved,

182
00:11:20,576 --> 00:11:23,579
or live as a witness to his treason.

183
00:11:23,663 --> 00:11:25,123
<i>A choice?</i>

184
00:11:25,665 --> 00:11:27,709
<i>Was a mere court lady</i>

185
00:11:27,792 --> 00:11:30,503
<i>ever afforded the right to choose?</i>

186
00:11:31,337 --> 00:11:34,507
Even if I stand at the crossroads
of life and death again,

187
00:11:34,590 --> 00:11:37,552
I will never cower behind a man.

188
00:11:40,513 --> 00:11:42,265
Are you making a proclamation now?

189
00:11:42,348 --> 00:11:44,892
Must we be this solemn at a stew place?

190
00:11:44,976 --> 00:11:46,853
I am just telling you where I stand.

191
00:11:46,936 --> 00:11:48,271
So bear that in mind.

192
00:11:48,354 --> 00:11:50,606
I <i>will</i> stand tall
on my own two feet in this life,

193
00:11:50,690 --> 00:11:51,566
without fail.

194
00:11:52,108 --> 00:11:53,985
Save the chatter and just support me.

195
00:11:58,531 --> 00:11:59,615
I'm sometimes

196
00:11:59,699 --> 00:12:01,743
overwhelmed by your sheer audacity.

197
00:12:03,286 --> 00:12:05,204
How commendable you are, Shin Seo-ri.

198
00:12:05,705 --> 00:12:06,748
I most certainly am.

199
00:12:07,332 --> 00:12:10,293
Tenacity like mine would even reduce
the Jade Emperor to tears.

200
00:12:14,797 --> 00:12:16,883
<i>I'll take care of it all, so don't worry.</i>

201
00:12:17,884 --> 00:12:20,720
What exactly is he taking care of?

202
00:12:26,392 --> 00:12:27,352
Grandfather.

203
00:12:28,061 --> 00:12:30,563
Goodness.
What brings you here at this hour?

204
00:12:35,151 --> 00:12:37,570
It seemed like
Se-gye was struggling a bit.

205
00:12:37,653 --> 00:12:40,156
May I step in, Grandfather?

206
00:12:43,034 --> 00:12:44,118
Take care.

207
00:12:44,911 --> 00:12:46,579
Why did you pay for that?

208
00:12:46,662 --> 00:12:50,541
I am a man with no history
of ever accepting a meal from a woman.

209
00:12:50,625 --> 00:12:52,293
And it had to be you, of all people.

210
00:12:52,377 --> 00:12:53,419
This doesn't count.

211
00:12:53,503 --> 00:12:54,545
It's not a real date.

212
00:12:54,629 --> 00:12:56,923
Did you expect me
to just continue freeloading?

213
00:12:57,006 --> 00:12:58,341
Freeloaders go bald.

214
00:12:58,424 --> 00:13:01,010
Someone's awfully scared of hair loss.
Women don't go bald.

215
00:13:01,094 --> 00:13:02,303
That is not true.

216
00:13:02,387 --> 00:13:05,056
Between endocrine disruptors
and microplastics,

217
00:13:05,139 --> 00:13:07,475
women are not immune to hair loss either.

218
00:13:07,558 --> 00:13:09,060
You've been quite the scholar tonight.

219
00:13:09,143 --> 00:13:10,228
Been hitting the books?

220
00:13:10,311 --> 00:13:12,897
Fearing I had become a dopamine addict,

221
00:13:12,980 --> 00:13:14,690
I traded Shorts for the newspaper.

222
00:13:15,858 --> 00:13:17,402
That's music to my ears.

223
00:13:17,485 --> 00:13:19,737
It seems your English has improved too.

224
00:13:19,821 --> 00:13:20,988
That…

225
00:13:21,823 --> 00:13:23,199
still remains out of reach.

226
00:13:23,908 --> 00:13:26,494
Speaking a different tongue
is harder than it looks.

227
00:13:29,580 --> 00:13:31,082
You still have a long way to go.

228
00:13:31,165 --> 00:13:34,085
English is a must if you want to be
a global superstar. What's your plan?

229
00:13:34,168 --> 00:13:36,337
If you're so worried, teach me yourself.

230
00:13:36,421 --> 00:13:38,506
I don't really have the time
to be a private tutor.

231
00:13:38,589 --> 00:13:39,549
But what can I do?

232
00:13:39,632 --> 00:13:41,050
What's the hourly rate?

233
00:13:41,134 --> 00:13:42,468
You are going to charge me?

234
00:13:42,552 --> 00:13:44,345
Of course. Who are you trying to swindle?

235
00:13:44,429 --> 00:13:46,764
-Nothing in life is free.
-I am no swindler!

236
00:13:50,309 --> 00:13:51,227
Get in.

237
00:13:58,067 --> 00:13:59,527
Sir, we have a big problem.

238
00:14:01,070 --> 00:14:02,113
CHIEF OF STAFF SON JAE-HAN

239
00:14:04,365 --> 00:14:07,535
CHAIL'S CHA SE-GYE
MOCHANG'S MO TAE-HEE CONFIRM RELATIONSHIP

240
00:14:11,873 --> 00:14:15,376
<i>The relationship between the heirs</i>
<i>of Chail and Mochang</i>

241
00:14:15,460 --> 00:14:17,336
<i>is drawing immense public attention.</i>

242
00:14:17,420 --> 00:14:19,839
<i>Insiders say Cha Se-gye,</i>
<i>the head of a cosmetics startup,</i>

243
00:14:19,922 --> 00:14:23,384
<i>and Mo Tae-hee,</i>
<i>the head of a jewelry brand,</i>

244
00:14:23,468 --> 00:14:25,803
<i>have recently begun</i>
<i>seeing each other quietly</i>

245
00:14:25,887 --> 00:14:28,556
<i>and are expected to tie the knot soon--</i>

246
00:14:30,016 --> 00:14:33,352
Our chairman appears to be
in quite a hurry.

247
00:14:33,436 --> 00:14:35,438
GRANDFATHER

248
00:14:41,444 --> 00:14:42,361
Hey.

249
00:14:43,946 --> 00:14:45,072
Why the long face?

250
00:14:46,073 --> 00:14:47,533
Why? Is someone cursing you out?

251
00:14:47,617 --> 00:14:49,619
Leaving malicious comments?
Should I reply for you?

252
00:14:49,702 --> 00:14:51,662
Stop it. I thought you were
on a dopamine detox.

253
00:14:51,746 --> 00:14:53,164
-I'm confiscating this.
-Give it back!

254
00:14:53,247 --> 00:14:56,375
Late-night scrolling
will rot your brain, you know.

255
00:14:56,459 --> 00:14:57,335
Hey.

256
00:14:58,044 --> 00:14:58,961
Just forget it.

257
00:14:59,045 --> 00:15:01,422
Let's turn off our phones
and focus on reality.

258
00:15:03,591 --> 00:15:05,092
How about <i>ramyeon</i> for round two?

259
00:15:05,176 --> 00:15:06,260
<i>Ramyeon?</i>

260
00:15:11,015 --> 00:15:14,519
<i>A man and a woman having </i>ramyeon
<i>at this late hour.</i>

261
00:15:14,602 --> 00:15:15,770
<i>That can only mean…</i>

262
00:15:19,857 --> 00:15:22,899
I am full as it is.
Why would we eat <i>ramyeon?</i>

263
00:15:22,985 --> 00:15:25,321
I'm suggesting it
because it's not just any <i>ramyeon.</i>

264
00:15:25,404 --> 00:15:27,782
-I wonder if they're open 24 hours.
-"24 hours"?

265
00:15:28,449 --> 00:15:30,146
You want to stay up all night…

266
00:15:30,701 --> 00:15:31,619
Gosh.

267
00:15:37,792 --> 00:15:39,126
OPEN 24 HOURS

268
00:15:39,210 --> 00:15:40,461
24 HOURS, OPEN 24 HOURS

269
00:15:40,545 --> 00:15:42,713
OPEN 24/7

270
00:15:45,800 --> 00:15:47,677
I am not ready for this step yet!

271
00:15:48,177 --> 00:15:49,679
Stop the car and give me my phone.

272
00:15:49,762 --> 00:15:51,138
What? Why do you want your phone?

273
00:15:51,222 --> 00:15:52,390
What do you mean, why?

274
00:15:52,473 --> 00:15:54,141
It is mine, so return it!

275
00:15:54,225 --> 00:15:55,184
Hold on.

276
00:15:55,268 --> 00:15:56,852
Jeez! Watch your hands!

277
00:15:56,936 --> 00:15:58,187
This is extortion!

278
00:15:58,271 --> 00:16:00,856
Kidnapping or extortion.
Think whatever you want--

279
00:16:00,940 --> 00:16:02,567
Hand it over! My phone!

280
00:16:03,901 --> 00:16:05,027
The <i>ramyeon</i> you mentioned…

281
00:16:05,111 --> 00:16:07,363
Not just any<i> ramyeon.</i>
It's <i>ramyeon </i>by the Hangang River.

282
00:16:07,446 --> 00:16:10,116
You should have it at least once
if you live in Seoul.

283
00:16:11,659 --> 00:16:12,868
Guess I was wrong.

284
00:16:16,831 --> 00:16:18,874
What's with the sudden disappointment?

285
00:16:18,958 --> 00:16:19,875
Well?

286
00:16:19,959 --> 00:16:21,168
What were you expecting?

287
00:16:22,253 --> 00:16:24,755
Were you hoping to share
a different kind of <i>ramyeon?</i>

288
00:16:24,839 --> 00:16:26,507
What absolute nonsense!

289
00:16:28,884 --> 00:16:32,555
Dragging me to the Hangang River
for some damn <i>ramyeon </i>when I am exhausted?

290
00:16:32,638 --> 00:16:34,599
Come on, it's nice and cool here.

291
00:16:35,391 --> 00:16:36,517
Feel it for yourself.

292
00:16:42,356 --> 00:16:44,483
<i>Now feel it for yourself.</i>

293
00:16:44,567 --> 00:16:45,901
<i>This cleansing chill.</i>

294
00:16:59,832 --> 00:17:00,958
<i>What is this?</i>

295
00:17:04,378 --> 00:17:05,421
What's wrong?

296
00:17:06,589 --> 00:17:07,590
You don't like it?

297
00:17:08,841 --> 00:17:11,719
You like the ocean,
so I figured you'd like the river too.

298
00:17:15,181 --> 00:17:17,016
Why are you looking at me like that?

299
00:17:18,184 --> 00:17:20,478
Are you amazed by my face again?

300
00:17:25,107 --> 00:17:26,233
Damn fool.

301
00:17:26,942 --> 00:17:28,611
That is a bountiful load of crap.

302
00:17:36,160 --> 00:17:38,871
Mr. Cha's DUI scandal has died down
following Shin Seo-ri's explanation

303
00:17:38,954 --> 00:17:40,915
and the rumors of him
dating the Mochang heir.

304
00:17:40,998 --> 00:17:43,209
As a result, the declining stock price
has reversed course

305
00:17:43,292 --> 00:17:44,460
in after-hours trading.

306
00:17:45,169 --> 00:17:46,837
He's quite lucky with women.

307
00:17:46,921 --> 00:17:50,132
Two women swooped in
like knights in shining armor to save him.

308
00:17:50,216 --> 00:17:51,425
Hold on.

309
00:17:51,509 --> 00:17:53,094
What in the world…

310
00:17:54,345 --> 00:17:56,430
The very embodiment of public deception.

311
00:17:57,056 --> 00:17:58,599
What are you complaining about now?

312
00:17:58,683 --> 00:17:59,684
She is not Nongae.

313
00:17:59,767 --> 00:18:01,769
What could this besotted mermaid
possibly teach?

314
00:18:01,852 --> 00:18:03,729
She threw everything away for a man.

315
00:18:03,813 --> 00:18:05,648
She deserves no statue.

316
00:18:05,731 --> 00:18:06,982
Stripped to the waist, no less.

317
00:18:07,066 --> 00:18:08,109
Stripped?

318
00:18:09,819 --> 00:18:12,863
Are you ever going to let go
of this method-acting business?

319
00:18:13,781 --> 00:18:16,075
Do you think this is
some monument to feminine virtue?

320
00:18:16,158 --> 00:18:17,410
It's not for that.

321
00:18:18,035 --> 00:18:19,286
-It is not?
-No, it's not.

322
00:18:20,663 --> 00:18:22,164
Then what is it for?

323
00:18:22,248 --> 00:18:24,083
It's for making wishes.

324
00:18:24,166 --> 00:18:26,335
They say if you rub its nose
and make a wish,

325
00:18:26,419 --> 00:18:27,962
it comes true or something.

326
00:18:29,046 --> 00:18:30,798
What utter nonsense.

327
00:18:32,258 --> 00:18:34,051
Look. See how its nose is worn down.

328
00:18:34,135 --> 00:18:36,303
It's really like that
from all the people rubbing it.

329
00:18:36,387 --> 00:18:37,805
I will not fall for that!

330
00:18:37,888 --> 00:18:39,682
You're treating me like some fool.

331
00:18:40,766 --> 00:18:41,684
Give me a second.

332
00:18:42,309 --> 00:18:43,436
Yes, Mr. Son.

333
00:18:47,773 --> 00:18:50,109
Cha Se-gye has been a bit antsy.

334
00:18:51,277 --> 00:18:53,320
I feel like he has something to tell me.

335
00:18:54,488 --> 00:18:55,364
Any updates?

336
00:18:55,448 --> 00:18:57,742
Given how quickly
the press release went out,

337
00:18:57,825 --> 00:18:59,410
it appears it was prepared in advance.

338
00:18:59,493 --> 00:19:02,121
Ms. Mo has said she wishes
to discuss it with you in person.

339
00:19:02,204 --> 00:19:04,415
So Grandfather
and Mo Tae-hee teamed up?

340
00:19:04,498 --> 00:19:05,708
<i>But what a relief.</i>

341
00:19:05,791 --> 00:19:07,251
<i>Instead of plummeting,</i>

342
00:19:07,334 --> 00:19:09,336
our shares shot to 80,000 won
thanks to this.

343
00:19:09,420 --> 00:19:10,755
It went up that much?

344
00:19:14,049 --> 00:19:15,134
Noted, for now.

345
00:19:20,014 --> 00:19:22,433
How am I going to tell her this?

346
00:19:22,516 --> 00:19:24,602
With that temper, I'll be in for a fight.

347
00:19:26,061 --> 00:19:27,730
How dare you cheat on me?

348
00:19:28,314 --> 00:19:30,608
Do you truly wish to lose your head?

349
00:19:33,736 --> 00:19:35,946
Man, I'd be lucky if she just got mad.

350
00:19:39,033 --> 00:19:40,743
To think you were cheating on me.

351
00:19:41,368 --> 00:19:44,079
To think I am fated to be
some lowly concubine.

352
00:19:58,928 --> 00:20:01,180
I really don't want to see her cry.

353
00:20:07,061 --> 00:20:08,187
What? Are you crying?

354
00:20:13,108 --> 00:20:14,902
I pray to you.

355
00:20:14,985 --> 00:20:17,446
I pray to you, River God Habaek.

356
00:20:17,530 --> 00:20:19,156
I thought you didn't believe it.

357
00:20:26,413 --> 00:20:27,414
Keep it down!

358
00:20:31,460 --> 00:20:32,795
Done praying? Come here.

359
00:20:32,878 --> 00:20:34,755
No, I still have more to say.

360
00:20:34,839 --> 00:20:36,507
Shin Seo-ri, I've been thinking.

361
00:20:37,341 --> 00:20:39,635
Like you said,
we dodged a bullet more or less.

362
00:20:39,718 --> 00:20:42,596
Well, there was
some unintended collateral damage,

363
00:20:42,680 --> 00:20:44,557
but it seems we've mostly recovered.

364
00:20:46,100 --> 00:20:47,017
Anyway,

365
00:20:47,101 --> 00:20:48,936
you rushing over saved the day.

366
00:20:49,019 --> 00:20:50,521
After nagging me this whole time,

367
00:20:50,604 --> 00:20:51,647
now you say it?

368
00:20:53,566 --> 00:20:55,860
Your explanation earlier
was pretty smooth.

369
00:20:56,402 --> 00:20:58,153
You were super quick on your feet.

370
00:20:58,696 --> 00:20:59,947
What did you say again?

371
00:21:00,030 --> 00:21:02,741
A fine face and noble character?

372
00:21:02,825 --> 00:21:03,826
Your "beloved."

373
00:21:04,410 --> 00:21:05,703
Unbelievable.

374
00:21:06,203 --> 00:21:07,872
Do you find me that great?

375
00:21:07,955 --> 00:21:09,039
What are you saying?

376
00:21:12,585 --> 00:21:15,212
So, are you going to allow me
to become your beloved?

377
00:21:17,089 --> 00:21:18,632
<i>Finally getting to the point?</i>

378
00:21:21,385 --> 00:21:24,722
Fine. Since we both know
how we really feel anyway,

379
00:21:24,805 --> 00:21:26,223
why play hard to get?

380
00:21:26,807 --> 00:21:28,183
It only eats you up inside.

381
00:21:28,684 --> 00:21:29,685
I shall hereby

382
00:21:30,603 --> 00:21:32,062
grant you my permission.

383
00:21:33,439 --> 00:21:35,274
-You grant me permission?
-Yes, I do.

384
00:21:36,567 --> 00:21:38,944
I will grant you the chance
to seize this opportunity,

385
00:21:39,028 --> 00:21:42,323
so stop hesitating
like a sad little puppy in the rain.

386
00:21:43,157 --> 00:21:44,408
"Seize this opportunity"?

387
00:21:45,826 --> 00:21:46,952
Seize this…

388
00:21:50,247 --> 00:21:51,248
"See each other?"

389
00:21:52,249 --> 00:21:53,959
You want to see each other?

390
00:21:54,043 --> 00:21:56,211
From what I have gathered,
"seeing each other"

391
00:21:56,295 --> 00:21:58,380
is a kind of testing-the-waters period.

392
00:21:58,464 --> 00:21:59,840
Let us fan this flicker.

393
00:21:59,924 --> 00:22:02,176
Who knows? This flicker might one day

394
00:22:02,718 --> 00:22:04,219
become an exquisite flourish.

395
00:22:05,262 --> 00:22:07,222
At my age, with my credentials,

396
00:22:07,306 --> 00:22:08,933
must I really go through a trial period?

397
00:22:09,016 --> 00:22:10,392
So, do you not want to?

398
00:22:11,435 --> 00:22:13,562
No, that's not what I'm saying.

399
00:22:13,646 --> 00:22:17,983
Then again, in today's cutthroat world,
nobody would just hire someone full-time

400
00:22:18,067 --> 00:22:20,402
without a trial period first.

401
00:22:25,491 --> 00:22:27,493
Then I should tell you the truth too.

402
00:22:29,870 --> 00:22:32,206
Can't keep secrets
from the woman I'm seeing.

403
00:22:32,289 --> 00:22:34,041
<i>Here it comes.</i>

404
00:22:34,583 --> 00:22:35,793
<i>I must remain composed.</i>

405
00:22:37,711 --> 00:22:38,671
So…

406
00:22:39,171 --> 00:22:40,422
I completely understand.

407
00:22:42,675 --> 00:22:44,551
So you need not hold back any longer.

408
00:22:48,055 --> 00:22:49,139
You understand?

409
00:22:49,848 --> 00:22:50,808
Of course.

410
00:22:53,060 --> 00:22:56,313
Just one look in your eyes,
and I know everything you want to say.

411
00:22:59,441 --> 00:23:00,484
But still,

412
00:23:00,567 --> 00:23:03,988
with a completely sober mind,
my heart is not quite ready yet.

413
00:23:04,071 --> 00:23:06,573
Damn it. I guess I made it obvious.

414
00:23:09,785 --> 00:23:12,705
I was going to tell you
when I thought you could handle it.

415
00:23:14,289 --> 00:23:16,125
But since you understand, we're set.

416
00:23:17,209 --> 00:23:18,669
You see, in the world I'm from,

417
00:23:18,752 --> 00:23:21,505
even this is a sort of
business arrangement. That's all.

418
00:23:22,965 --> 00:23:25,426
But just in case,
let me make this clear now.

419
00:23:26,885 --> 00:23:28,429
I never asked for any of this.

420
00:23:29,013 --> 00:23:30,514
I was just suddenly handed a fiancée.

421
00:23:30,597 --> 00:23:31,849
I also have my grievances--

422
00:23:31,932 --> 00:23:32,933
What did you say?

423
00:23:33,851 --> 00:23:34,852
What fiancée?

424
00:23:38,814 --> 00:23:39,982
Damn it to hell.

425
00:23:40,065 --> 00:23:41,817
CHA SE-GYE AND MO TAE-HEE
CONFIRM RELATIONSHIP

426
00:23:42,443 --> 00:23:43,485
Rotten scoundrels…

427
00:23:47,906 --> 00:23:49,742
Hey, what are you doing?

428
00:23:49,825 --> 00:23:51,285
Is it not obvious? I'm planting seeds.

429
00:23:51,368 --> 00:23:53,037
Not even seedlings?
They'll take forever to grow.

430
00:23:53,120 --> 00:23:54,580
I am not trying to grow food.

431
00:23:54,663 --> 00:23:56,415
Just suppressing my urge to kill.

432
00:23:56,498 --> 00:23:59,293
If anyone crosses me right now,
heads will roll.

433
00:23:59,376 --> 00:24:01,503
That is why I must find solace in nature.

434
00:24:02,087 --> 00:24:03,797
You're not making any sense.

435
00:24:03,881 --> 00:24:04,965
Hold on.

436
00:24:05,507 --> 00:24:07,009
Those are nice photos.

437
00:24:07,092 --> 00:24:08,973
They look really good together,
don't they?

438
00:24:09,595 --> 00:24:10,804
Wow.

439
00:24:11,597 --> 00:24:13,599
-They certainly do not!
-What the--

440
00:24:13,682 --> 00:24:14,767
Are you nuts?

441
00:24:14,850 --> 00:24:17,436
They do look good together.
See for yourself.

442
00:24:17,519 --> 00:24:18,604
Damn it.

443
00:24:28,530 --> 00:24:29,531
Se-gye.

444
00:24:39,958 --> 00:24:41,335
Grandfather, let's go to the study.

445
00:24:41,418 --> 00:24:43,045
No, we can just talk here.

446
00:24:44,338 --> 00:24:46,840
Tae-hee will be
part of our family soon anyway.

447
00:24:46,924 --> 00:24:47,800
What's there to hide?

448
00:24:47,883 --> 00:24:50,135
Se-gye, don't worry about the controversy.

449
00:24:50,219 --> 00:24:53,722
Tae-hee, you should stop contacting
my grandfather behind my back.

450
00:24:53,806 --> 00:24:55,057
It makes us both look bad.

451
00:24:55,140 --> 00:24:56,558
Watch your mouth.

452
00:24:57,059 --> 00:24:58,435
I guess I was too hasty.

453
00:24:58,519 --> 00:25:00,896
I was worried you'd suffer
from false rumors,

454
00:25:00,979 --> 00:25:02,689
so I rushed things.

455
00:25:12,491 --> 00:25:14,076
What are you trying to do here?

456
00:25:15,202 --> 00:25:17,162
I just moved up the timeline

457
00:25:17,246 --> 00:25:18,288
for going public a bit.

458
00:25:18,372 --> 00:25:19,832
I didn't discuss it with you

459
00:25:19,915 --> 00:25:22,459
because I wanted to save you
from the other rumors quickly.

460
00:25:22,543 --> 00:25:23,752
That was my oversight.

461
00:25:23,836 --> 00:25:26,421
You seem to be suffering
from a serious misunderstanding.

462
00:25:26,505 --> 00:25:27,881
A strategic marriage to whitewash

463
00:25:27,965 --> 00:25:29,758
my half-breed chaebol image
doesn't interest me.

464
00:25:29,842 --> 00:25:31,802
-I no longer need to do that.
-Why not?

465
00:25:33,053 --> 00:25:34,388
Is it because of that woman,

466
00:25:34,471 --> 00:25:35,472
Shin Seo-ri?

467
00:25:40,018 --> 00:25:40,936
That's right.

468
00:25:41,019 --> 00:25:43,063
She's the only thing
I care about right now.

469
00:25:43,147 --> 00:25:45,107
So let's stop
with these sudden declarations of yours.

470
00:25:45,190 --> 00:25:47,067
Then why did you show up
for the blind date?

471
00:25:47,151 --> 00:25:49,486
It's rude to the woman
you're obsessed with

472
00:25:49,570 --> 00:25:50,988
and to me.

473
00:25:53,699 --> 00:25:54,700
I know.

474
00:25:55,367 --> 00:25:57,452
You two haven't been together that long.

475
00:25:57,536 --> 00:26:00,497
A relationship can heat up quickly
with the right spark,

476
00:26:00,581 --> 00:26:02,499
but it can cool down just as fast.

477
00:26:03,542 --> 00:26:04,835
I'll wait.

478
00:26:06,128 --> 00:26:07,254
As long as it takes.

479
00:26:09,047 --> 00:26:11,258
Seo-ri, you should be careful
around Mr. Cha.

480
00:26:11,341 --> 00:26:13,051
No good comes from a spokesperson

481
00:26:13,135 --> 00:26:15,804
appearing too close to the company CEO.

482
00:26:15,888 --> 00:26:18,015
It's the perfect setup for weird gossip.

483
00:26:18,098 --> 00:26:20,058
Are we in Joseon?
That is some archaic nonsense.

484
00:26:20,142 --> 00:26:21,894
You need to trust me on this, kid.

485
00:26:21,977 --> 00:26:23,979
A single scandal will sink
a nobody like you

486
00:26:24,062 --> 00:26:25,022
straight to the bottom.

487
00:26:25,105 --> 00:26:26,690
What was that? A <i>nobody?</i>

488
00:26:26,773 --> 00:26:27,816
-Why you…
-Oh, come on.

489
00:26:31,069 --> 00:26:33,739
And work on that damn temper of yours.

490
00:26:33,822 --> 00:26:36,992
If you go full prima donna
after landing one supporting role…

491
00:26:39,912 --> 00:26:42,539
Anyway, getting tangled up
with a taken man

492
00:26:42,623 --> 00:26:44,541
will leave your image beyond repair.

493
00:26:44,625 --> 00:26:47,544
So just be mindful of your conduct.

494
00:26:48,128 --> 00:26:50,380
<i>Why are you so gloomy?</i>
<i>It doesn't suit you at all.</i>

495
00:26:50,464 --> 00:26:53,300
A female friend is no match
for a real girlfriend anyway.

496
00:26:53,800 --> 00:26:55,052
Real girlfriend, my foot.

497
00:26:55,636 --> 00:26:57,262
Can you not tell just by looking?

498
00:26:57,346 --> 00:26:59,431
They are obviously just business partners.

499
00:26:59,514 --> 00:27:00,891
Just business partners?

500
00:27:01,516 --> 00:27:02,643
No wonder.

501
00:27:02,726 --> 00:27:05,103
I couldn't see any chemistry between them.

502
00:27:05,187 --> 00:27:06,146
Right?

503
00:27:06,230 --> 00:27:08,398
There is nothing going on between them.

504
00:27:08,482 --> 00:27:09,650
Wait a minute.

505
00:27:10,192 --> 00:27:12,319
That would make it a "contract" romance.

506
00:27:12,402 --> 00:27:14,238
That changes everything.

507
00:27:14,863 --> 00:27:16,907
-They're seeing this through.
-Through to where?

508
00:27:16,990 --> 00:27:19,201
Think about it.
What's the cardinal rule of K-romance?

509
00:27:19,284 --> 00:27:21,328
Contract romance,
contract marriage, contract divorce.

510
00:27:21,411 --> 00:27:24,873
Every contract between a man
and a woman eventually leads to love.

511
00:27:24,957 --> 00:27:26,708
Therefore, even when their contract ends,

512
00:27:26,792 --> 00:27:29,503
it's an unwritten rule
that they'll be bound forever.

513
00:27:29,586 --> 00:27:30,796
Baek Gwang-nam.

514
00:27:34,049 --> 00:27:36,426
Shall I bind your trap shut forever?

515
00:27:43,058 --> 00:27:44,184
Sir.

516
00:27:45,519 --> 00:27:47,980
Did Ms. Shin take it okay?

517
00:27:48,063 --> 00:27:50,148
With that temper of hers,
I doubt she just accepted it.

518
00:27:50,232 --> 00:27:52,109
She didn't even flinch.

519
00:27:52,192 --> 00:27:54,413
She said she couldn't care less
about a loveless fiancée.

520
00:27:55,404 --> 00:27:56,321
<i>A fiancée.</i>

521
00:27:56,405 --> 00:27:57,447
A fiancée?

522
00:27:57,531 --> 00:27:58,407
A fiancée.

523
00:27:58,490 --> 00:27:59,825
A fiancée…

524
00:28:01,118 --> 00:28:03,328
As if a loveless fiancée is some big deal.

525
00:28:03,412 --> 00:28:05,257
I could not care less.

526
00:28:06,206 --> 00:28:07,332
I'm completely unfazed.

527
00:28:07,416 --> 00:28:08,834
This is a serious problem.

528
00:28:08,917 --> 00:28:09,918
What is?

529
00:28:10,002 --> 00:28:12,713
She can't be that beautiful
and also be so understanding, right?

530
00:28:13,755 --> 00:28:14,715
Right?

531
00:28:17,134 --> 00:28:18,468
Gosh.

532
00:28:21,888 --> 00:28:23,307
Is he an idiot?

533
00:28:26,935 --> 00:28:27,936
Is it a gift?

534
00:28:28,020 --> 00:28:29,479
Yes, for my son.

535
00:28:30,063 --> 00:28:31,189
He likes baseball.

536
00:28:31,273 --> 00:28:32,482
Then,

537
00:28:32,566 --> 00:28:33,692
how about this one?

538
00:28:33,775 --> 00:28:34,818
It's cowhide,

539
00:28:34,901 --> 00:28:36,611
so the leather is soft enough for kids.

540
00:28:36,695 --> 00:28:38,905
No thanks. He won't be using it anyway.

541
00:28:40,407 --> 00:28:41,283
She has arrived.

542
00:28:41,366 --> 00:28:42,826
Please wrap this one up.

543
00:28:43,785 --> 00:28:45,495
-Adult size.
-Sure.

544
00:28:54,755 --> 00:28:56,256
<i>I also thought long and hard</i>

545
00:28:56,340 --> 00:28:59,509
about how much I stand to gain
from this potential union.

546
00:28:59,593 --> 00:29:02,721
Secure friendly shares to survive
the Chail Group power struggle to start.

547
00:29:02,804 --> 00:29:04,473
Rehabilitate my tarnished image as CEO.

548
00:29:04,556 --> 00:29:07,059
I realized the gains
were surprisingly substantial.

549
00:29:09,102 --> 00:29:10,812
Your path to the throne.

550
00:29:10,896 --> 00:29:13,231
I'm confident I could clear it for you.

551
00:29:13,982 --> 00:29:15,108
That's the problem.

552
00:29:15,734 --> 00:29:17,027
I'm not so confident

553
00:29:18,070 --> 00:29:20,197
I could give her up without regretting it.

554
00:29:20,906 --> 00:29:22,949
In other words,

555
00:29:23,033 --> 00:29:23,950
<i>I've made my choice.</i>

556
00:29:24,034 --> 00:29:25,118
Says who?

557
00:29:30,123 --> 00:29:31,917
It's been a while, Ms. Mo.

558
00:29:35,629 --> 00:29:37,839
-It has. Here for a meeting?
-Yes.

559
00:29:37,923 --> 00:29:39,966
-Have you been well?
-Oh right.

560
00:29:42,719 --> 00:29:43,762
I saw the article.

561
00:29:43,845 --> 00:29:46,431
When did things progress so far?
Truth be told,

562
00:29:46,515 --> 00:29:47,474
I was surprised.

563
00:29:47,557 --> 00:29:49,059
I told you.

564
00:29:49,142 --> 00:29:51,395
I fell for Se-gye at first sight.

565
00:29:53,188 --> 00:29:55,482
Must've been an impressive first meeting.

566
00:29:55,565 --> 00:29:57,901
Yes, it was impressive.

567
00:29:58,944 --> 00:30:01,279
<i>He left quite an intense first impression.</i>

568
00:30:01,363 --> 00:30:04,074
CHA SE-GYE, CEO OF BIOJEI
GRANDSON OF CHAIL GROUP CHAIRMAN

569
00:30:04,991 --> 00:30:07,119
<i>Enough to make him unforgettable.</i>

570
00:30:08,662 --> 00:30:09,871
<i>It sounds a bit childish,</i>

571
00:30:09,955 --> 00:30:13,125
<i>but I wanted to leave one on him as well.</i>

572
00:30:16,253 --> 00:30:17,421
Oh my God!

573
00:30:17,504 --> 00:30:19,423
Gosh. Oh no…

574
00:30:19,506 --> 00:30:21,091
I'm so sorry.

575
00:30:26,513 --> 00:30:27,889
Damn it.

576
00:30:27,973 --> 00:30:30,684
Oh my, I'm so sorry. Are you okay?

577
00:30:30,767 --> 00:30:33,228
That blind date is with me.

578
00:30:33,979 --> 00:30:36,022
Give me a chance to apologize properly.

579
00:30:37,691 --> 00:30:40,485
<i>I thought that chance had finally come.</i>

580
00:30:40,569 --> 00:30:41,653
CHA SE-GYE

581
00:30:41,736 --> 00:30:44,239
So you're just going
to continue ignoring my calls?

582
00:30:45,615 --> 00:30:46,950
Too bad.

583
00:30:47,033 --> 00:30:49,619
-This is just getting me more fired up.
<i>-The number…</i>

584
00:30:51,705 --> 00:30:54,374
Yes, Mr. Park. Release the file.

585
00:30:54,458 --> 00:30:55,500
Right now.

586
00:31:03,049 --> 00:31:06,178
You said marriage was the only way
to clean up a half-breed chaebol image.

587
00:31:06,261 --> 00:31:07,679
I see you chose strategic marriage.

588
00:31:07,762 --> 00:31:09,306
It's just business.

589
00:31:09,389 --> 00:31:10,682
I'll end it after this wraps up.

590
00:31:10,765 --> 00:31:13,226
Really? Why are you so blasé about it?

591
00:31:13,310 --> 00:31:15,979
Could it be because of that woman?

592
00:31:16,646 --> 00:31:17,564
What woman?

593
00:31:17,647 --> 00:31:18,565
You're dating.

594
00:31:19,191 --> 00:31:20,859
The one you said you care about.

595
00:31:20,942 --> 00:31:23,487
How do I know?
I'm an expert in this field.

596
00:31:23,570 --> 00:31:25,947
If I couldn't figure that out,
I'd have to quit.

597
00:31:26,907 --> 00:31:27,782
Right.

598
00:31:27,866 --> 00:31:30,619
Hey, since we're on the topic,
let me ask you something.

599
00:31:32,204 --> 00:31:34,498
She has some strange quirks.

600
00:31:34,581 --> 00:31:36,374
-As strange as you?
-Just listen.

601
00:31:37,167 --> 00:31:38,919
She can get a bit too intense sometimes.

602
00:31:39,002 --> 00:31:41,379
Always going on about life and death,
this lifetime, and whatnot.

603
00:31:41,463 --> 00:31:42,964
Needlessly dramatic.

604
00:31:43,048 --> 00:31:45,342
Like she's hung up
on some failed past life.

605
00:31:48,303 --> 00:31:50,222
Should she see a doctor?

606
00:31:50,305 --> 00:31:52,015
Well, that's great.

607
00:31:52,098 --> 00:31:54,476
You can bond over healing
in therapy like a happy couple.

608
00:31:54,559 --> 00:31:56,102
We're not a couple.

609
00:31:57,103 --> 00:31:59,314
"Happy couple"?

610
00:32:03,568 --> 00:32:04,861
Are you saying we're both insane?

611
00:32:04,945 --> 00:32:06,530
Damn it.

612
00:32:07,072 --> 00:32:09,491
I should charge double
for a compatibility reading.

613
00:32:09,574 --> 00:32:10,951
Darn it.

614
00:32:11,993 --> 00:32:13,745
Let's see here.

615
00:32:14,371 --> 00:32:16,706
The dragon-in-waiting meets
a typhoon in a drought

616
00:32:16,790 --> 00:32:18,917
and finally ascends.

617
00:32:19,000 --> 00:32:20,210
The clouds part

618
00:32:20,293 --> 00:32:22,504
and the sun rises.

619
00:32:22,587 --> 00:32:23,547
Gosh!

620
00:32:24,089 --> 00:32:25,507
The dragon-in-waiting ascended.

621
00:32:25,590 --> 00:32:27,300
Does that mean I will achieve my goal?

622
00:32:27,384 --> 00:32:30,512
If it ascends before becoming
a dragon, it's bound to fall.

623
00:32:31,346 --> 00:32:33,557
But the clouds parted, and the sun rose.

624
00:32:33,640 --> 00:32:34,724
A drought needs rain.

625
00:32:34,808 --> 00:32:36,685
If the sun rose, you're ruined.

626
00:32:36,768 --> 00:32:38,353
"DR." Doomed romance.

627
00:32:39,187 --> 00:32:40,272
Damn it.

628
00:32:41,690 --> 00:32:43,358
You do not know
what you are talking about.

629
00:32:43,441 --> 00:32:45,110
Sounds like you are making it up.

630
00:32:45,193 --> 00:32:46,945
No wonder you are stuck in this tent.

631
00:32:47,571 --> 00:32:49,614
Can you even afford rent on this place?

632
00:32:50,282 --> 00:32:51,658
I'd like to.

633
00:32:51,741 --> 00:32:54,619
I was once the 18th direct disciple
of the Celestial Maiden of Mount Jiri.

634
00:32:54,703 --> 00:32:56,079
I used to be hot stuff.

635
00:32:56,162 --> 00:32:59,082
I just blew the price of an apartment
on training fees for absolutely nothing.

636
00:32:59,165 --> 00:33:00,584
What? A whole apartment?

637
00:33:00,667 --> 00:33:01,751
Yes.

638
00:33:03,086 --> 00:33:03,962
Damn swindler…

639
00:33:04,629 --> 00:33:06,131
Where is it?

640
00:33:07,257 --> 00:33:08,633
You said Mount Jiri.

641
00:33:08,717 --> 00:33:10,343
She came down a while ago.

642
00:33:10,427 --> 00:33:12,637
These days, celestial maidens, generals,

643
00:33:12,721 --> 00:33:16,600
and all the mystics reside in Gangnam now.

644
00:33:16,683 --> 00:33:18,435
It has been a while.

645
00:33:21,688 --> 00:33:24,441
-What brings you here?
-Well, I…

646
00:33:27,068 --> 00:33:29,487
They say even a monk
cannot shave his own head.

647
00:33:29,571 --> 00:33:31,865
The Celestial Maiden of Mount Jiri
should know why I am here

648
00:33:31,948 --> 00:33:32,866
with just a glance, no?

649
00:33:34,951 --> 00:33:35,827
How dare you!

650
00:33:37,871 --> 00:33:40,165
So you want a compatibility reading.

651
00:33:41,708 --> 00:33:44,669
I pray to you, great spirit. I pray.

652
00:33:44,753 --> 00:33:46,379
Come now.

653
00:33:53,303 --> 00:33:54,304
My word.

654
00:33:55,180 --> 00:33:56,181
A cursed bond.

655
00:33:56,264 --> 00:33:57,515
Mortal enemies.

656
00:33:58,058 --> 00:34:01,353
So cosmically at odds,
they should never cross paths again.

657
00:34:05,732 --> 00:34:07,942
And yet, there may just be

658
00:34:08,026 --> 00:34:10,028
a way around it.

659
00:34:11,029 --> 00:34:12,739
What? With a talisman?

660
00:34:14,949 --> 00:34:17,243
How dare you try to swindle me as well!

661
00:34:17,952 --> 00:34:20,789
How dare you!
Are you calling me a swindler?

662
00:34:20,872 --> 00:34:22,957
Do you dare show
such irreverence in the presence

663
00:34:23,041 --> 00:34:24,250
of the Celestial Maiden?

664
00:34:24,334 --> 00:34:25,460
Do you?

665
00:34:31,007 --> 00:34:33,760
Have you been going around
saying I swindled you?

666
00:34:33,843 --> 00:34:36,179
Gosh. No, of course not.

667
00:34:36,262 --> 00:34:38,556
How could I do that to my great master?

668
00:34:38,640 --> 00:34:42,185
You said the training fees you paid
could buy a whole apartment.

669
00:34:42,268 --> 00:34:44,104
Well, actually, if we take

670
00:34:44,187 --> 00:34:46,022
inflation into consideration,

671
00:34:46,106 --> 00:34:48,400
-it'd be a high-rise--
-Yes, a high-rise!

672
00:34:48,942 --> 00:34:50,944
I have never seen
such a swindler in my life.

673
00:34:51,027 --> 00:34:52,112
Do as I say

674
00:34:52,195 --> 00:34:54,155
while I still ask nicely. Full refund.

675
00:34:54,239 --> 00:34:55,240
Full!

676
00:34:57,742 --> 00:34:58,743
Hey!

677
00:34:58,827 --> 00:35:00,787
Drag them out of here right now!

678
00:35:02,706 --> 00:35:03,832
Oh boy.

679
00:35:05,375 --> 00:35:07,377
Why, hello. Hey there.

680
00:35:07,460 --> 00:35:10,630
I highly recommend
just holding back if you can.

681
00:35:11,673 --> 00:35:12,966
Come on now.

682
00:35:13,049 --> 00:35:15,301
Just try laying a single finger on me.

683
00:35:16,386 --> 00:35:17,262
Why, I oughta!

684
00:35:17,929 --> 00:35:19,472
What are you standing around for?

685
00:35:19,556 --> 00:35:21,808
I told you to drag them out right now!

686
00:35:21,891 --> 00:35:23,518
Yeah, bring it on.

687
00:35:25,937 --> 00:35:28,940
I shall use your limbs
to fold you like a paper boat.

688
00:35:47,292 --> 00:35:48,668
What sort of training did they do?

689
00:35:48,752 --> 00:35:51,546
How does their martial prowess
surpass neighborhood thugs?

690
00:35:51,629 --> 00:35:53,381
They almost snapped my ankle off.

691
00:35:54,466 --> 00:35:56,509
You can't compare
undisciplined street thugs

692
00:35:56,593 --> 00:35:59,929
to devotees who trek barefoot
through Mount Jiri like them.

693
00:36:00,430 --> 00:36:01,306
Come on now.

694
00:36:01,389 --> 00:36:03,349
I don't even know
why you suddenly offered

695
00:36:03,433 --> 00:36:05,185
to get me a refund I never asked for.

696
00:36:05,268 --> 00:36:06,728
Ridiculous.

697
00:36:07,729 --> 00:36:09,063
Here, take one.

698
00:36:12,567 --> 00:36:14,110
To recharge.

699
00:36:16,279 --> 00:36:18,072
Wow, it's good.

700
00:36:18,156 --> 00:36:19,741
I feel a surge of energy.

701
00:36:21,326 --> 00:36:23,536
You feel reenergized? Gosh.

702
00:36:23,620 --> 00:36:24,621
Brazen wretches.

703
00:36:26,039 --> 00:36:27,791
I shall hone my martial prowess

704
00:36:27,874 --> 00:36:29,626
and secure that refund for you.

705
00:36:29,709 --> 00:36:31,252
I told you. I don't need no refund!

706
00:36:31,336 --> 00:36:33,755
Unbelievable.

707
00:36:37,425 --> 00:36:39,511
My goodness. Such a malevolent formation.

708
00:36:41,679 --> 00:36:43,348
Maybe it really is a cursed bond.

709
00:36:48,770 --> 00:36:50,396
Shin Seo-ri, what happened to your face?

710
00:36:50,480 --> 00:36:51,689
Did you get into a fight?

711
00:36:52,857 --> 00:36:55,568
There was no fight.
Just a one-sided beatdown.

712
00:36:55,652 --> 00:36:56,778
What have you been up to?

713
00:36:56,861 --> 00:36:58,530
-Hey, let me see that.
-Goodness.

714
00:36:58,613 --> 00:37:00,406
-Jeez, your cheek is…
-Goodness me, that aches.

715
00:37:00,490 --> 00:37:02,492
Did you actually go one-on-one?

716
00:37:06,162 --> 00:37:07,789
What are we going to do…

717
00:37:07,872 --> 00:37:09,707
I was wondering who had
the gall to seize

718
00:37:09,791 --> 00:37:11,000
the dressing room.

719
00:37:11,084 --> 00:37:13,378
Who knew it would be
just some random extras?

720
00:37:16,214 --> 00:37:17,841
I should head to my next scene.

721
00:37:20,301 --> 00:37:21,803
This is why

722
00:37:21,886 --> 00:37:24,430
people need to know their place.

723
00:37:24,514 --> 00:37:26,850
In this industry,
if you splash in waters too deep,

724
00:37:26,933 --> 00:37:29,185
you could be drowning
in sewage in an instant.

725
00:37:30,186 --> 00:37:32,981
As if someone like her
could ever seduce a chaebol.

726
00:37:37,235 --> 00:37:38,528
"Seduce"?

727
00:37:40,530 --> 00:37:41,614
What?

728
00:37:41,698 --> 00:37:43,825
"Jilted Actress A."

729
00:37:43,908 --> 00:37:45,159
Isn't that you?

730
00:37:45,243 --> 00:37:48,246
WASHED-UP CHILD STAR'S PIPE DREAM
SEDUCTION OF ENGAGED CHAEBOL FIZZLES

731
00:37:48,329 --> 00:37:49,539
WAS IT A CINDERELLA FANTASY?

732
00:37:51,791 --> 00:37:54,836
Mr. Son, did you find out
who first leaked this to the tabloids?

733
00:37:54,919 --> 00:37:57,130
Well, a reporter contact confirmed it was

734
00:37:57,213 --> 00:37:58,715
Mochang's External Relations Office.

735
00:37:58,798 --> 00:38:00,091
Mochang?

736
00:38:04,304 --> 00:38:05,346
I mean, sure,

737
00:38:05,430 --> 00:38:07,265
I get that you want to marry rich.

738
00:38:07,348 --> 00:38:08,224
Even so,

739
00:38:08,308 --> 00:38:10,476
you still should've picked
a league within your reach.

740
00:38:10,560 --> 00:38:11,686
Jilted…

741
00:38:11,769 --> 00:38:13,479
Seriously? That's so cringe.

742
00:38:13,563 --> 00:38:14,480
That's so tacky.

743
00:38:14,564 --> 00:38:16,274
I was planning to lead a quiet life,

744
00:38:16,357 --> 00:38:19,277
yet you keep flapping your gums
like you are untouchable.

745
00:38:19,360 --> 00:38:21,446
What? "Flapping my gums"?

746
00:38:23,114 --> 00:38:23,990
Listen, minx.

747
00:38:24,073 --> 00:38:27,035
Even if I splash too hard and end up
drowning in sewage like you said,

748
00:38:27,118 --> 00:38:28,244
I have nothing to lose.

749
00:38:28,328 --> 00:38:29,454
But I believe your situation

750
00:38:29,537 --> 00:38:30,663
is quite different.

751
00:38:30,747 --> 00:38:32,248
Am I wrong?

752
00:38:35,710 --> 00:38:36,920
<i>Former Child Actor A.</i>

753
00:38:37,003 --> 00:38:38,838
<i>Known as the Queen of the Night.</i>

754
00:38:38,922 --> 00:38:41,299
<i>From her cosmetics ad</i>
<i>to her minor role in a historical drama,</i>

755
00:38:41,382 --> 00:38:44,218
<i>industry insiders say a shady deal</i>
<i>is behind her comeback.</i>

756
00:38:44,302 --> 00:38:46,804
<i>After failing to seduce a chaebol,</i>
<i>she now faces ruin.</i>

757
00:38:46,888 --> 00:38:48,222
They ought to be deep-fried alive.

758
00:38:48,306 --> 00:38:49,849
How are they coming up with such lies?

759
00:38:52,477 --> 00:38:53,686
But are you sure "Actress A"

760
00:38:53,770 --> 00:38:55,229
is Shin Seo-ri?

761
00:38:55,313 --> 00:38:56,606
Yeah, I'm sure.

762
00:38:56,689 --> 00:38:59,275
I got the tip from the manager
of another actor at her agency.

763
00:38:59,359 --> 00:39:00,610
I'm 100% sure.

764
00:39:02,153 --> 00:39:03,696
Could that be Yoon Ji-hyo's manager?

765
00:39:03,780 --> 00:39:05,073
Yeah, how'd you know?

766
00:39:05,156 --> 00:39:06,407
-Mommy!
-Jesus!

767
00:39:06,491 --> 00:39:08,868
The scum of the earth!

768
00:39:08,952 --> 00:39:10,912
Sneaking around
like a little rat for a picture?

769
00:39:10,995 --> 00:39:12,413
Are you nuts?

770
00:39:12,497 --> 00:39:13,623
That is worth a fortune!

771
00:39:13,706 --> 00:39:16,250
You had no problem stealing my face
without knowing its worth.

772
00:39:16,334 --> 00:39:17,210
Steal?

773
00:39:17,293 --> 00:39:18,962
We do this because the public
has a right to know--

774
00:39:19,045 --> 00:39:20,588
The right to know? Really?

775
00:39:20,672 --> 00:39:22,465
Then I should expose
your mugs for all to see.

776
00:39:22,548 --> 00:39:25,593
Shall I have you doxxed
until you cannot leave your house?

777
00:39:25,677 --> 00:39:26,678
Why, you little…

778
00:39:28,012 --> 00:39:29,389
Hand over the phone!

779
00:39:34,978 --> 00:39:37,605
As I thought.
I have not lost my touch yet.

780
00:39:49,701 --> 00:39:51,619
Is crossing lines your hobby?

781
00:39:51,703 --> 00:39:53,121
You're basically asking for a fight.

782
00:39:53,204 --> 00:39:54,914
Se-gye, you like
"give and take," don't you?

783
00:39:54,998 --> 00:39:58,292
I believe our dating rumor saved
Biojei's stock from plummeting.

784
00:39:58,376 --> 00:40:01,254
With that in mind,
I'd like to make a proposal.

785
00:40:01,337 --> 00:40:03,881
So you gave,
and now you want to take?

786
00:40:03,965 --> 00:40:04,882
Let's hear it.

787
00:40:04,966 --> 00:40:07,093
Treat me properly as your fiancée.

788
00:40:07,176 --> 00:40:09,012
How about making me your partner

789
00:40:09,095 --> 00:40:10,930
for this weekend's launch party?

790
00:40:11,014 --> 00:40:12,890
Our first official photo op

791
00:40:12,974 --> 00:40:14,434
since the dating announcement.

792
00:40:14,517 --> 00:40:15,893
A couple shot?

793
00:40:15,977 --> 00:40:18,563
You want the partner spot
over the official brand ambassador.

794
00:40:18,646 --> 00:40:21,065
Yes. At this point, even for Ms. Shin,

795
00:40:21,149 --> 00:40:24,444
a public appearance together
would surely be too much for her.

796
00:40:24,527 --> 00:40:27,113
I'd be satisfied with just this for now.

797
00:40:27,655 --> 00:40:28,740
Not too hard, right?

798
00:40:32,827 --> 00:40:34,954
I was worried about that too,

799
00:40:35,580 --> 00:40:38,458
but you have suddenly provided
some clarity on the matter.

800
00:40:41,085 --> 00:40:42,003
CHIEF OF STAFF SON JAE-HAN

801
00:40:43,421 --> 00:40:44,422
Go ahead, Mr. Son.

802
00:40:44,505 --> 00:40:47,175
<i>Sir, we have a big problem.</i>
<i>It's regarding Ms. Shin.</i>

803
00:40:47,258 --> 00:40:48,384
What about Shin Seo-ri now?

804
00:40:48,468 --> 00:40:49,510
She just

805
00:40:50,136 --> 00:40:52,221
made a major score!

806
00:40:52,305 --> 00:40:55,433
<i>Self-proclaimed Celestial Maiden</i>
<i>and cult leader Choi was arrested</i>

807
00:40:55,516 --> 00:40:58,186
<i>with her followers after a tip-off</i>
<i>from actress Shin Seo-ri.</i>

808
00:40:58,269 --> 00:40:59,771
Police arrested Ms. Choi on the 7th

809
00:40:59,854 --> 00:41:02,231
on charges of repeatedly torturing
and assaulting followers

810
00:41:02,315 --> 00:41:05,026
under the claim that they were
possessed by evil spirits.

811
00:41:05,109 --> 00:41:07,028
Investigators also found she had embezzled

812
00:41:07,111 --> 00:41:09,363
large sums from followers
as "training fees"

813
00:41:09,447 --> 00:41:12,366
and evaded
roughly 1.5 billion won in taxes.

814
00:41:12,450 --> 00:41:13,993
When the police raided the shrine,

815
00:41:14,077 --> 00:41:16,829
<i>they discovered her believers</i>
<i>were inhaling drugs during training,</i>

816
00:41:16,913 --> 00:41:18,289
<i>sending further shockwaves.</i>

817
00:41:18,372 --> 00:41:20,541
<i>Shin visited the shrine</i>
<i>to research for her current role,</i>

818
00:41:20,625 --> 00:41:23,002
<i>where she obtained evidence</i>
<i>of these activities</i>

819
00:41:23,086 --> 00:41:24,921
<i>and requested an investigation.</i>

820
00:41:26,172 --> 00:41:27,215
Of course.

821
00:41:27,298 --> 00:41:29,634
Gosh, you even drink water
with such pizzazz.

822
00:41:29,717 --> 00:41:30,927
They were right.

823
00:41:31,010 --> 00:41:33,721
Muddy waters are best overturned
by a much larger wave.

824
00:41:33,805 --> 00:41:34,680
<i>Hey, reporter lords.</i>

825
00:41:34,764 --> 00:41:37,225
Instead of tailing a small fry like me,

826
00:41:37,308 --> 00:41:38,518
how about we negotiate?

827
00:41:38,601 --> 00:41:39,852
This scoop will easily pay off

828
00:41:39,936 --> 00:41:41,854
the cost of that camera.

829
00:41:41,938 --> 00:41:43,314
-A scoop?
-A scoop?

830
00:41:43,397 --> 00:41:44,273
Hey!

831
00:41:44,357 --> 00:41:45,608
Drag them both out this instant!

832
00:41:45,691 --> 00:41:46,567
Come on!

833
00:41:47,735 --> 00:41:48,861
Oh boy.

834
00:41:50,279 --> 00:41:51,489
Why, hello.

835
00:41:56,452 --> 00:41:57,995
<i>Just look at this lot.</i>

836
00:41:58,079 --> 00:41:59,622
<i>Their eyes are all glazed over.</i>

837
00:41:59,705 --> 00:42:00,832
I knew it.

838
00:42:00,915 --> 00:42:02,875
No amount of training barefoot

839
00:42:02,959 --> 00:42:05,128
can match the martial prowess
of those street thugs.

840
00:42:05,211 --> 00:42:09,006
Your Highness, how did you know
they were high on drugs?

841
00:42:09,882 --> 00:42:12,593
During my court maid days,
I met a physician who ruined his life

842
00:42:12,677 --> 00:42:14,512
after becoming addicted to poppies.

843
00:42:14,595 --> 00:42:16,097
By poppies, you mean…

844
00:42:16,180 --> 00:42:17,515
Opium.

845
00:42:18,057 --> 00:42:19,976
-Opium…
-It was a precious medicine

846
00:42:20,059 --> 00:42:21,185
used by the Royal Infirmary,

847
00:42:21,269 --> 00:42:22,979
but some fell under its spell

848
00:42:23,062 --> 00:42:25,022
and ruined their lives.

849
00:42:26,315 --> 00:42:28,192
The glazed eyes of those addicts

850
00:42:28,276 --> 00:42:29,527
looked exactly like theirs.

851
00:42:31,404 --> 00:42:33,406
Gosh, Your Highness.

852
00:42:33,489 --> 00:42:35,408
-Goodness.
-You're the best.

853
00:42:35,491 --> 00:42:37,160
That is right. Yes indeed.

854
00:42:37,243 --> 00:42:38,661
There's no one like you.

855
00:42:38,744 --> 00:42:39,996
That is right.

856
00:42:43,666 --> 00:42:45,209
Regarding this weekend,

857
00:42:45,293 --> 00:42:47,003
it'd be best to make separate plans.

858
00:42:47,086 --> 00:42:48,212
What?

859
00:42:48,296 --> 00:42:50,256
But earlier, you said you would--

860
00:42:50,339 --> 00:42:52,758
I said I found clarity.
I never said I'd go with you.

861
00:42:52,842 --> 00:42:54,177
You should always hear people out.

862
00:42:54,260 --> 00:42:57,054
I was just looking to shield her
from unnecessary drama.

863
00:42:57,138 --> 00:42:58,764
But after listening to you,

864
00:42:58,848 --> 00:43:00,892
I'm even more certain
about going with her.

865
00:43:00,975 --> 00:43:03,477
We did nothing wrong,
so there's no reason to hide.

866
00:43:03,561 --> 00:43:05,563
A friendly couple shot with Shin Seo-ri.

867
00:43:09,483 --> 00:43:12,445
You think one lousy article
is going to elevate that woman?

868
00:43:21,537 --> 00:43:22,663
Watch your mouth.

869
00:43:23,206 --> 00:43:25,458
I never intended to be
your partner in the first place.

870
00:43:25,541 --> 00:43:27,001
Quit coming after my woman

871
00:43:27,084 --> 00:43:28,586
with your petty little games.

872
00:43:30,338 --> 00:43:32,006
That's what I came to say.

873
00:43:32,089 --> 00:43:34,133
Let's make this our last meeting.

874
00:43:34,217 --> 00:43:37,303
Go through my office
until the broken engagement is announced.

875
00:43:40,389 --> 00:43:44,018
<i>The actress who schooled a cult is</i>
<i>officially on her way to superstardom.</i>

876
00:43:44,101 --> 00:43:47,605
<i>Officially stanning Shin Seo-ri now.</i>
<i>Hoping her next project is action.</i>

877
00:43:48,856 --> 00:43:50,650
<i>Dumb luck served justice.</i>
<i>Two birds, one stone.</i>

878
00:43:50,733 --> 00:43:52,485
<i>At this point, she's destined for success.</i>

879
00:43:52,568 --> 00:43:53,736
How dare they!

880
00:43:53,819 --> 00:43:55,363
"Dumb luck"?

881
00:43:55,905 --> 00:43:57,323
More like, "sharp instinct."

882
00:44:18,803 --> 00:44:19,720
Who are you?

883
00:44:24,141 --> 00:44:26,060
President Choi Mun-do sent me.

884
00:44:40,199 --> 00:44:42,076
He's waiting. Please come with me.

885
00:44:54,297 --> 00:44:55,589
Ms. Shin Seo-ri.

886
00:44:55,673 --> 00:44:58,009
I guess you're more understanding
than you let on.

887
00:44:58,092 --> 00:44:59,260
Enough to let

888
00:44:59,343 --> 00:45:01,429
Cha Se-gye get engaged to another woman?

889
00:45:01,512 --> 00:45:03,514
What are you scheming?
And what is that photo about?

890
00:45:03,597 --> 00:45:04,724
As I've said before,

891
00:45:04,807 --> 00:45:07,059
I'm giving you an opportunity here.

892
00:45:07,143 --> 00:45:09,520
A chance to save yourself
and your family.

893
00:45:10,229 --> 00:45:12,982
Break up Se-gye and Mochang.

894
00:45:13,566 --> 00:45:14,775
By whatever means necessary.

895
00:45:17,403 --> 00:45:20,323
A single photo of you two
leaving a hotel should do it.

896
00:45:21,115 --> 00:45:22,366
Are you telling me

897
00:45:22,908 --> 00:45:25,202
to manufacture a sordid scandal?

898
00:45:26,579 --> 00:45:27,955
Is that it?

899
00:45:28,956 --> 00:45:31,292
You have nothing to lose from this.

900
00:45:31,375 --> 00:45:33,836
But Cha Se-gye
must have lost his mind.

901
00:45:33,919 --> 00:45:35,296
To save you,

902
00:45:35,379 --> 00:45:37,673
he went ahead with an engagement
that wasn't even planned.

903
00:45:37,757 --> 00:45:38,841
Thanks to that,

904
00:45:38,924 --> 00:45:40,634
my position has become unstable.

905
00:45:44,263 --> 00:45:45,473
You have two weeks.

906
00:45:46,724 --> 00:45:47,808
Destruction deadline.

907
00:45:56,317 --> 00:45:58,819
<i>As long as the Grand Prince</i>
<i>remains out of His favor,</i>

908
00:45:58,903 --> 00:46:00,279
<i>he will not survive.</i>

909
00:46:01,072 --> 00:46:02,740
So make your choice.

910
00:46:02,823 --> 00:46:05,117
Die as the Grand Prince's beloved,

911
00:46:05,201 --> 00:46:08,037
or live as a witness to his treason.

912
00:46:17,004 --> 00:46:18,339
What brings you here…

913
00:46:25,304 --> 00:46:26,722
Dan-sim of the Kang clan.

914
00:46:26,806 --> 00:46:28,307
I knew you would turn out

915
00:46:28,391 --> 00:46:30,059
to be quite useful.

916
00:46:30,142 --> 00:46:33,562
To get close to my brother this quickly…

917
00:46:34,480 --> 00:46:35,606
I have not.

918
00:46:36,190 --> 00:46:37,733
How could someone like me--

919
00:46:38,776 --> 00:46:40,611
That is the proof.

920
00:46:41,404 --> 00:46:44,240
You likely took it
not knowing what it was.

921
00:46:44,323 --> 00:46:46,742
This was a gift from our older brother,

922
00:46:46,826 --> 00:46:48,244
the late Crown Prince,

923
00:46:48,327 --> 00:46:50,204
to his youngest brother.

924
00:46:51,664 --> 00:46:53,040
The late Crown Prince…

925
00:46:53,124 --> 00:46:53,999
Yes.

926
00:46:54,083 --> 00:46:57,378
A keepsake from my poor brother
who burned to death.

927
00:46:59,255 --> 00:47:01,257
And he gifted that keepsake to you?

928
00:47:01,799 --> 00:47:03,801
What do you think that means?

929
00:47:03,884 --> 00:47:05,344
That must mean

930
00:47:06,429 --> 00:47:08,055
you are somewhat special to him.

931
00:47:09,682 --> 00:47:11,142
Would you not agree?

932
00:47:29,076 --> 00:47:30,661
Even I would find it grievous

933
00:47:31,662 --> 00:47:33,747
to have my younger brother's neck snapped

934
00:47:33,831 --> 00:47:36,083
in the flower of his youth.

935
00:47:37,543 --> 00:47:39,170
So how about this?

936
00:47:40,129 --> 00:47:42,298
His honor will be tarnished,

937
00:47:43,090 --> 00:47:44,800
but his life will remain intact.

938
00:47:45,426 --> 00:47:47,845
Compared to plotting high treason…

939
00:47:49,847 --> 00:47:51,640
harassing a court lady

940
00:47:52,475 --> 00:47:53,976
is a much lighter offense, no?

941
00:47:55,561 --> 00:47:56,520
What does that…

942
00:47:59,106 --> 00:48:01,484
You have until early tomorrow afternoon.

943
00:48:44,777 --> 00:48:45,861
<i>Of course I was terrified.</i>

944
00:48:45,945 --> 00:48:48,364
Afraid you'd get dragged
through the mud with me.

945
00:48:49,240 --> 00:48:50,115
It scared me.

946
00:48:50,199 --> 00:48:52,910
You like the ocean,
so I figured you'd like the river too.

947
00:48:52,993 --> 00:48:54,078
<i>Feel it for yourself.</i>

948
00:48:54,161 --> 00:48:55,579
Now feel it for yourself.

949
00:48:56,413 --> 00:48:57,706
<i>This cleansing chill.</i>

950
00:49:11,512 --> 00:49:13,556
Why are you home so late,
Champion of Justice?

951
00:49:14,723 --> 00:49:16,850
<i>Cha Se-gye, it appears</i>

952
00:49:16,934 --> 00:49:19,770
<i>I am fated to curse the men around me.</i>

953
00:49:20,854 --> 00:49:22,439
<i>Wherever I settle,</i>

954
00:49:22,523 --> 00:49:24,483
<i>desolation follows.</i>

955
00:49:37,288 --> 00:49:38,956
What brings you here unannounced?

956
00:49:40,833 --> 00:49:43,544
We're seeing each other.
Surprises are allowed.

957
00:49:44,753 --> 00:49:47,256
How's my surprise visit?
Is your heart fluttering?

958
00:49:52,469 --> 00:49:53,470
You fool.

959
00:49:54,763 --> 00:49:56,265
Damn.

960
00:49:56,348 --> 00:49:59,143
They say love makes you a fool.

961
00:49:59,935 --> 00:50:03,022
I never knew what that meant,
but now I finally get it.

962
00:50:06,984 --> 00:50:09,028
Pull yourself together, Cha Se-gye.

963
00:50:09,778 --> 00:50:10,696
Neither of us

964
00:50:11,363 --> 00:50:13,657
has the time to get giddy
over playing house.

965
00:50:13,741 --> 00:50:14,825
No.

966
00:50:16,243 --> 00:50:17,202
I'm going to.

967
00:50:18,370 --> 00:50:20,039
That's exactly what I'll do.

968
00:50:20,122 --> 00:50:21,915
My whole life was black or white,

969
00:50:21,999 --> 00:50:23,375
ally or enemy.

970
00:50:23,459 --> 00:50:25,252
It was like living in a war zone.

971
00:50:25,336 --> 00:50:26,503
But you…

972
00:50:27,630 --> 00:50:29,214
You're my first real ally.

973
00:50:29,882 --> 00:50:32,760
Someone I could never
weigh the pros and cons of.

974
00:50:32,843 --> 00:50:34,136
You're the only one.

975
00:50:36,639 --> 00:50:38,057
-The only one?
-Yeah.

976
00:50:39,099 --> 00:50:40,851
You're the only one, Shin Seo-ri.

977
00:50:47,274 --> 00:50:48,400
So…

978
00:50:49,985 --> 00:50:52,821
when it's just us,
we can be a little immature.

979
00:50:56,241 --> 00:50:58,702
Screw this damn world,

980
00:50:59,286 --> 00:51:00,746
and let your heart flutter with me.

981
00:51:10,172 --> 00:51:11,590
Let me be your only one too.

982
00:51:33,237 --> 00:51:34,363
THE WOMEN'S KINGDOM SEASON 2

983
00:51:34,446 --> 00:51:36,782
EPISODE 7

984
00:51:37,866 --> 00:51:40,536
I clearly said once my illness
shows signs of recovery,

985
00:51:40,619 --> 00:51:42,871
I would pay my respects to the Queen.

986
00:51:42,955 --> 00:51:44,289
How dare you act so impertinently

987
00:51:44,373 --> 00:51:46,125
as if I were some criminal?

988
00:51:48,168 --> 00:51:49,712
It is the Queen's order.

989
00:51:49,795 --> 00:51:50,879
Please understand.

990
00:51:52,297 --> 00:51:54,883
Did you convey the state
of my illness correctly?

991
00:51:54,967 --> 00:51:56,802
You thought you could look down on me.

992
00:51:56,885 --> 00:51:58,470
Do you still see me as nothing more

993
00:51:58,554 --> 00:52:00,931
than some lowly court lady
who waits on you?

994
00:52:02,933 --> 00:52:04,643
Tell the Queen!

995
00:52:04,727 --> 00:52:06,270
<i>That I will pay my respects</i>

996
00:52:06,353 --> 00:52:08,105
<i>once my condition improves.</i>

997
00:52:08,188 --> 00:52:10,107
She's the real final boss.

998
00:52:10,190 --> 00:52:12,025
That's a solid wrist snap.

999
00:52:12,109 --> 00:52:13,277
I knew she'd do that.

1000
00:52:13,360 --> 00:52:15,654
She has the face of a man-eater.
A nine-tailed fox.

1001
00:52:15,738 --> 00:52:17,614
Has this old hag lost her mind?

1002
00:52:17,698 --> 00:52:19,032
Who you calling a nine-tailed fox?

1003
00:52:19,116 --> 00:52:21,076
Her eyes are slanted upwards.

1004
00:52:21,160 --> 00:52:22,745
She totally looks like a fox.

1005
00:52:22,828 --> 00:52:23,954
Shut your mouth.

1006
00:52:24,037 --> 00:52:26,081
It takes one to know one.

1007
00:52:26,165 --> 00:52:27,750
You want me to rip your eyes out?

1008
00:52:27,833 --> 00:52:29,710
-Try it.
-Come here, you.

1009
00:52:29,793 --> 00:52:30,794
-Crazy?
-Why you--

1010
00:52:30,878 --> 00:52:31,795
Try it! Go on!

1011
00:52:31,879 --> 00:52:33,338
That's enough talk. Come here now.

1012
00:52:33,422 --> 00:52:34,423
-Stop it.
-Here I come!

1013
00:52:34,506 --> 00:52:36,008
Come on. I'm waiting.

1014
00:52:36,091 --> 00:52:37,718
-Please stop.
-Oh shush.

1015
00:52:37,801 --> 00:52:42,556
SONGJIN GENERAL HOSPITAL

1016
00:52:49,396 --> 00:52:51,231
Hey, why the long face again?

1017
00:52:51,315 --> 00:52:53,150
Something bothering you again?

1018
00:52:54,318 --> 00:52:56,069
Why did you not speak up earlier?

1019
00:52:56,862 --> 00:52:58,071
That I am your grandkid.

1020
00:52:59,406 --> 00:53:00,282
You saw that?

1021
00:53:00,365 --> 00:53:02,826
<i>By chance, are you embarrassed by me?</i>

1022
00:53:02,910 --> 00:53:04,453
Because it is embarrassing.

1023
00:53:04,536 --> 00:53:05,621
Embarrassing?

1024
00:53:05,704 --> 00:53:07,164
Of course it is.

1025
00:53:11,502 --> 00:53:13,629
An old ghost like me acting up…

1026
00:53:13,712 --> 00:53:15,380
What good would that do you?

1027
00:53:17,966 --> 00:53:21,428
So stop coming down here
and just focus on your work.

1028
00:53:21,512 --> 00:53:23,180
Strike while the iron is hot.

1029
00:53:23,263 --> 00:53:26,350
If I want to see you,
I can just watch you on TV.

1030
00:53:27,810 --> 00:53:29,061
Right?

1031
00:53:35,359 --> 00:53:36,777
Seo-ri.

1032
00:53:36,860 --> 00:53:37,903
You just focus on worrying

1033
00:53:37,986 --> 00:53:39,279
about your own future.

1034
00:53:39,988 --> 00:53:41,865
Turn a deaf ear to the nonsense,

1035
00:53:41,949 --> 00:53:44,117
and just keep moving forward.

1036
00:53:59,800 --> 00:54:01,510
<i>Can I really do that?</i>

1037
00:54:02,427 --> 00:54:03,720
<i>Will it be okay</i>

1038
00:54:04,847 --> 00:54:05,848
<i>if I do that?</i>

1039
00:54:06,849 --> 00:54:08,100
You…

1040
00:54:10,727 --> 00:54:13,856
more than deserve to be happy.

1041
00:54:19,987 --> 00:54:21,780
Oh, my baby.

1042
00:54:50,434 --> 00:54:52,394
Red was definitely the right choice.

1043
00:54:58,233 --> 00:54:59,443
So pretty.

1044
00:55:01,445 --> 00:55:02,863
Truly beautiful.

1045
00:55:18,837 --> 00:55:19,838
I'll do it tomorrow.

1046
00:55:34,478 --> 00:55:36,813
-What is the matter?
-In that well…

1047
00:55:37,564 --> 00:55:38,857
In the well…

1048
00:55:48,158 --> 00:55:49,368
My goodness!

1049
00:55:50,077 --> 00:55:52,162
<i>You are hereby placed under arrest.</i>

1050
00:55:52,245 --> 00:55:53,789
What harassment?

1051
00:55:54,414 --> 00:55:56,041
That is completely absurd.

1052
00:55:56,124 --> 00:55:58,418
How could Father believe
such a sordid rumor?

1053
00:56:05,550 --> 00:56:07,135
Dan-sim of the Kang clan?

1054
00:56:08,387 --> 00:56:10,389
If you wish to save that girl,

1055
00:56:10,472 --> 00:56:12,057
submit peacefully.

1056
00:56:25,028 --> 00:56:27,072
Geum-ok was my colleague.

1057
00:56:28,031 --> 00:56:30,450
A few days ago,
I realized she was with child.

1058
00:56:31,076 --> 00:56:33,662
Last night,
I asked again who fathered the child.

1059
00:56:35,622 --> 00:56:37,791
She named Grand Prince Cheongheon

1060
00:56:37,874 --> 00:56:39,835
before doing this…

1061
00:56:39,918 --> 00:56:41,586
While on night watch,

1062
00:56:41,670 --> 00:56:44,214
I saw that girl sneaking
into Grand Prince Cheongheon's quarters

1063
00:56:44,297 --> 00:56:45,632
with my own two eyes.

1064
00:56:50,721 --> 00:56:53,807
Proof of your scandal
runs so deep it spills over.

1065
00:56:53,890 --> 00:56:56,226
Do you still refuse to admit your crimes?

1066
00:56:57,060 --> 00:56:58,687
Is she safe?

1067
00:56:58,770 --> 00:57:00,939
It all hangs
on what comes out of your mouth.

1068
00:57:01,023 --> 00:57:02,441
How will you proceed?

1069
00:57:02,524 --> 00:57:04,568
If you will make me a binding promise…

1070
00:57:08,196 --> 00:57:10,782
I shall do as Your Highness wishes.

1071
00:57:13,285 --> 00:57:15,078
You wish to strike a deal?

1072
00:57:16,204 --> 00:57:19,291
It appears you have yet to grasp
the gravity of the situation.

1073
00:57:20,292 --> 00:57:21,376
Bring her in.

1074
00:57:48,487 --> 00:57:49,488
I…

1075
00:57:51,073 --> 00:57:52,991
wish to tell the truth.

1076
00:57:53,533 --> 00:57:55,118
Shortly after

1077
00:57:55,202 --> 00:57:57,954
I was assigned to his quarters…

1078
00:57:59,831 --> 00:58:01,333
His Highness

1079
00:58:01,416 --> 00:58:03,293
tried to force himself on me as well.

1080
00:58:08,048 --> 00:58:10,008
This is the evidence.

1081
00:58:12,010 --> 00:58:13,136
You…

1082
00:58:13,220 --> 00:58:14,429
Evidence?

1083
00:58:27,192 --> 00:58:28,276
Why, this is…

1084
00:58:32,280 --> 00:58:35,283
My brother, the Crown Prince,
gifted this to him.

1085
00:58:35,367 --> 00:58:37,369
How is this in your possession?

1086
00:58:38,870 --> 00:58:40,872
His Highness told me to keep it

1087
00:58:42,332 --> 00:58:44,042
as a token of affection.

1088
00:58:45,210 --> 00:58:48,380
I was beyond shocked and bewildered…

1089
00:58:52,134 --> 00:58:54,719
that I begged him to rescind it.

1090
00:58:54,803 --> 00:58:55,846
Enough.

1091
00:59:08,483 --> 00:59:11,069
But he insisted so heavily…

1092
00:59:11,153 --> 00:59:12,279
That is enough.

1093
00:59:16,700 --> 00:59:17,868
It is true.

1094
00:59:20,537 --> 00:59:23,498
I engaged in illicit relations
with the court ladies.

1095
00:59:23,582 --> 00:59:24,499
Therefore,

1096
00:59:25,041 --> 00:59:27,043
I ask you to spare this court lady

1097
00:59:27,127 --> 00:59:29,379
and punish me as you see fit.

1098
01:00:09,461 --> 01:00:12,005
<i>Even if I stand at the crossroads</i>
<i>of life and death again,</i>

1099
01:00:12,088 --> 01:00:15,133
I will never cower behind a man.

1100
01:00:15,217 --> 01:00:16,259
I…

1101
01:00:17,677 --> 01:00:19,346
wish to tell the truth.

1102
01:00:20,513 --> 01:00:23,016
<i>I am truly glad to be alive.</i>

1103
01:00:23,099 --> 01:00:25,060
<i>What, are you back from the dead?</i>

1104
01:00:25,143 --> 01:00:27,270
I am so happy to be alive.

1105
01:00:27,354 --> 01:00:29,189
<i>What is your name?</i>

1106
01:00:32,484 --> 01:00:35,403
Of course, my name is…

1107
01:00:50,794 --> 01:00:53,463
You told me
to bring everything, so I did,

1108
01:00:53,546 --> 01:00:54,714
but what is all this?

1109
01:00:54,798 --> 01:00:58,385
Designers are begging me
to wear their clothes. How could I refuse?

1110
01:00:58,468 --> 01:00:59,636
Champion of Justice…

1111
01:01:00,762 --> 01:01:02,931
Wait. Does this look better?

1112
01:01:03,014 --> 01:01:05,183
Why are you changing again?

1113
01:01:06,101 --> 01:01:08,478
I have snagged
every last bit of luxury today.

1114
01:01:08,561 --> 01:01:09,813
I am the main character today.

1115
01:01:16,194 --> 01:01:18,989
Ms. Shin, you should leave now.

1116
01:01:19,072 --> 01:01:20,240
Says who?

1117
01:01:20,323 --> 01:01:21,658
I am the main character today.

1118
01:01:22,367 --> 01:01:23,827
You appear to be an uninvited guest.

1119
01:01:23,910 --> 01:01:26,413
Looks like you had some fun
with that flash of good press,

1120
01:01:26,496 --> 01:01:28,123
but that's as far as you'll go.

1121
01:01:28,206 --> 01:01:31,418
I am far more suited to stand by his side
than someone whose reputation

1122
01:01:31,501 --> 01:01:34,462
can be made or broken
by a single tabloid rumor, no?

1123
01:01:36,006 --> 01:01:37,590
It was you.

1124
01:01:37,674 --> 01:01:39,791
You are the instigator of my scandal.

1125
01:01:39,866 --> 01:01:41,219
That's right.

1126
01:01:41,303 --> 01:01:43,763
You were starting
to get on my nerves, you see.

1127
01:01:43,847 --> 01:01:46,516
So I'd like for you to get lost now.

1128
01:01:46,599 --> 01:01:48,518
Get lost? What am I, a puppy?

1129
01:01:49,394 --> 01:01:50,270
Listen closely.

1130
01:01:50,353 --> 01:01:52,022
I live for today.

1131
01:01:54,065 --> 01:01:56,776
I have to strike while the iron is hot
and push forward.

1132
01:01:56,860 --> 01:01:58,695
So spare me the rest of your drivel,

1133
01:01:59,529 --> 01:02:01,281
and quietly get lost yourself.

1134
01:02:06,411 --> 01:02:08,872
Sounds like you're not afraid of anything.

1135
01:02:08,955 --> 01:02:10,040
Then how about this?

1136
01:02:10,123 --> 01:02:12,917
"The unfilial granddaughter who abandoned
her only flesh and blood,

1137
01:02:13,001 --> 01:02:14,210
her grandmother with dementia."

1138
01:02:14,294 --> 01:02:15,545
Or this one might work too.

1139
01:02:16,338 --> 01:02:19,466
"The parasitic grandmother
who bled her actress granddaughter dry."

1140
01:02:19,549 --> 01:02:20,759
"Debt scandal."

1141
01:02:21,468 --> 01:02:22,427
Do you

1142
01:02:23,595 --> 01:02:24,721
have a death wish?

1143
01:02:28,725 --> 01:02:30,643
Finally hit a nerve, did I?

1144
01:02:31,436 --> 01:02:32,812
I guess you cherish your family?

1145
01:02:33,855 --> 01:02:35,815
Then go take care
of your sick grandmother.

1146
01:02:35,899 --> 01:02:39,152
Stop forgetting your place,
trying to steal another woman's man.

1147
01:02:40,153 --> 01:02:42,238
Who says he is your man?

1148
01:02:42,322 --> 01:02:43,865
From what I hear,

1149
01:02:43,948 --> 01:02:46,034
you have been conspiring
from the shadows.

1150
01:02:47,077 --> 01:02:48,703
Let me give you some advice.

1151
01:02:49,245 --> 01:02:50,830
If you want to win a man's heart,

1152
01:02:50,914 --> 01:02:52,665
you should stop acting

1153
01:02:52,749 --> 01:02:55,418
like an anxious dog, whining at the door.

1154
01:02:55,502 --> 01:02:57,170
You would scare away any man like that.

1155
01:02:57,253 --> 01:02:58,463
What?

1156
01:02:59,005 --> 01:03:00,673
Why, you crazy bitch.

1157
01:03:11,434 --> 01:03:12,310
Se-gye.

1158
01:03:13,228 --> 01:03:14,104
You…

1159
01:03:15,355 --> 01:03:17,107
Shin Seo-ri, we need to talk.

1160
01:03:36,751 --> 01:03:38,211
Did you summon her?

1161
01:03:39,254 --> 01:03:41,923
I would have prepared myself
if I had known earlier.

1162
01:03:43,508 --> 01:03:44,843
She barged in so suddenly.

1163
01:03:45,385 --> 01:03:47,679
I almost grabbed her by the hair.

1164
01:03:47,762 --> 01:03:50,181
If we were caught on camera,
we would be in quite a bind.

1165
01:03:50,265 --> 01:03:51,558
I almost got canceled.

1166
01:03:54,602 --> 01:03:55,812
What is it?

1167
01:03:55,895 --> 01:03:57,063
Why are you staring?

1168
01:04:00,942 --> 01:04:02,902
Well, too bad if you are disappointed.

1169
01:04:02,986 --> 01:04:05,196
You cannot take back seeing each other.

1170
01:04:05,280 --> 01:04:07,407
You know my temper well enough.

1171
01:04:08,616 --> 01:04:10,160
There is no point in regretting it now.

1172
01:04:10,243 --> 01:04:11,286
Who are you?

1173
01:04:13,413 --> 01:04:14,664
You…

1174
01:04:17,500 --> 01:04:18,668
What do you mean, who?

1175
01:04:20,420 --> 01:04:22,005
Are you still half-asleep?

1176
01:04:23,256 --> 01:04:24,591
You cannot come dressed like this.

1177
01:04:24,674 --> 01:04:25,717
You should change first--

1178
01:04:25,800 --> 01:04:26,801
Dan-sim.

1179
01:04:32,348 --> 01:04:33,224
Kang.

1180
01:04:35,310 --> 01:04:36,478
Dan-sim.

1181
01:04:40,565 --> 01:04:42,150
What did you just…

1182
01:04:42,233 --> 01:04:43,401
Dan-sim of the Kang clan.

1183
01:04:45,028 --> 01:04:46,237
Who are you?

1184
01:04:48,823 --> 01:04:50,074
How…

1185
01:04:57,040 --> 01:04:58,791
Who are you really?

1186
01:05:04,672 --> 01:05:06,508
<i>Why do you stare at it so intently?</i>

1187
01:05:06,591 --> 01:05:10,053
<i>Does a plum blossom flowering</i>
<i>in midsummer unsettle you so?</i>

1188
01:05:10,136 --> 01:05:12,805
<i>Yes, it is quite an unsettling sight.</i>

1189
01:05:14,474 --> 01:05:16,684
<i>I gaze upon the flower</i>
<i>blooming out of season</i>

1190
01:05:17,393 --> 01:05:18,603
<i>because it is unsettling</i>

1191
01:05:19,729 --> 01:05:21,189
<i>and pitiable.</i>

1192
01:05:50,134 --> 01:05:53,429
MY ROYAL NEMESIS

1193
01:06:24,150 --> 01:06:25,150
-Shin Seo-ri.
-Gosh!

1194
01:06:25,259 --> 01:06:27,171
<i>Grandfather, I need</i>
<i>to introduce you to someone.</i>

1195
01:06:27,255 --> 01:06:29,048
Nice to meet you, Grandpapa!

1196
01:06:29,132 --> 01:06:30,425
<i>The Women's Kingdom?</i>

1197
01:06:30,508 --> 01:06:31,426
<i>"Consummation"?</i>

1198
01:06:31,509 --> 01:06:32,635
Your Majesty!

1199
01:06:33,261 --> 01:06:34,887
This is bull…

1200
01:06:34,971 --> 01:06:37,599
-What was it replaced with?
<i>-The Sericulture Rite scene.</i>

1201
01:06:37,682 --> 01:06:40,018
<i>Thanks to you, I totally stole that scene.</i>

1202
01:06:40,101 --> 01:06:41,102
Sickeningly sweet.

1203
01:06:41,185 --> 01:06:42,812
How could they lose a patient?

1204
01:06:42,895 --> 01:06:45,231
<i>She must be kept</i>
<i>from making any outside contact.</i>

1205
01:06:45,315 --> 01:06:46,858
<i>A woman keeps appearing in my dreams.</i>

1206
01:06:46,941 --> 01:06:48,234
<i>It seemed like that man</i>

1207
01:06:48,318 --> 01:06:51,404
<i>felt a deep yearning</i>
<i>for that woman named Kang Dan-sim.</i>

1208
01:06:51,487 --> 01:06:52,697
<i>What if it were not a dream?</i>

1209
01:06:52,780 --> 01:06:56,200
<i>If I were that woman, Kang Dan-sim,</i>
<i>what would you do?</i>

1210
01:06:58,038 --> 01:07:00,038
Subtitle translation by Justin S. Kim

